subSubSection.paragraph:
All the populations of 

P. klapperichi

are considered as a single species, because all of them share the following female genitalic characters: 
1
) spermatheca large and markedly longer than the whole sclerotized part of female genitalia; 
2
) spermathecal gland about as large as hemisternite.
